# Agent Platform Conventions

- Model every tenant-facing assistant as a canonical `agent_instances` record before wiring provider runtime details.
- Keep tier semantics explicit:
  - `simple` -> fast default experiences (typically Telnyx-backed)
  - `advanced` -> in-house orchestration with tools/MCP/RAG
  - `third_party` -> external provider orchestration (e.g. Abacus)
- Route all message processing through a single router (`routeAgentChat`) so telemetry and usage accounting stay consistent.
- Use provider drivers to isolate vendor specifics; avoid embedding provider logic directly in route handlers.
- Use promotion records (`agent_promotions`) whenever tier/provider changes so evolution history is preserved.
- For listing directory use cases, bind entries through `agent_listing_bindings` rather than encoding listing IDs inside arbitrary metadata.
